{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-1020"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Seafood Processing Operations"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1020"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :food/seafood-processing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :food-safety :fair-labor :marine-sustainability]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :seafood-processing-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "SeafoodProcessingAdvisor ⊣ SeafoodProcessingGovernor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph (langgraph.graph, seafoodprocessing.operation/build),
 append-only audit ledger (seafoodprocessing.store/ledger +
 append-ledger!, newly added to MemStore alongside its existing
 batch-metadata BatchStore protocol, which is unchanged). Fixes a
 structural gap: `deps.edn` declared `io.github.kotoba-lang/langgraph`
 only under an unused `:dev :override-deps` alias (`:deps {}` at top
 level, so the dependency was never actually resolved), and
 `operation.cljc`'s `run-operation` was a plain `let`-threaded
 advisor -> governor -> phase pipeline with zero `langgraph.graph`
 calls anywhere. Now: a genuinely compiled StateGraph (`:intake ->
 :advise -> :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit / :request-approval ->
 :commit / :hold`) with `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` +
 in-memory checkpointer for real human-in-the-loop resume. The
 Governor (independent food-safety checks: cold-chain temperature
 window, holding time, histamine assay, sanitation score, metal
 detector pass, evidence-checklist completeness, contamination-flag
 resolution, shelf-life, handoff well-formedness) and rollout phase
 gate (`seafoodprocessing.phase`) were already real logic; both are
 preserved unchanged, only wired into real graph nodes. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:coordinate-shipment` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-food-safety-concern`).
 `:log-production-batch` and `:coordinate-shipment` are high-stakes and
 ALWAYS escalate to a human plant operator via the compiled graph's
 `:request-approval` node (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based
 resume) when the Governor is clean, proven by
 `test/seafoodprocessing/operation_test.cljc` exercising commit /
 hard-hold (temperature violation) / phase-lock-hold / escalate-approve
 / escalate-reject through the REAL compiled graph end to end, plus a
 `clojure -M:dev:run` demo runner producing real ledger entries. 31
 tests / 128 assertions green (`clojure -M:dev:test`), clj-kondo 0
 errors."}
